message: Use vial on solids (e.g., amber, unicorn horn) to create extracts (value 30). Use filter on raw liquids (e.g., honey nectar, tree sap) for filtered liquids (value 30). Combine two *same-feature* liquids (magical with magical, mundane with mundane) that are either extracts or filtered to reach 60. AVOID combining liquids and gases directly, as this results in negative values. However, if you do, filtering the negative combined item can dramatically increase its value. Do NOT use vial on gas, and avoid filtering extracts directly as it often leads to 'poorly-filtered' items. Don't overdo it; if you hit 60, submitting is often a good strategy.

message: Focus on using tools first: Vials work best on raw solid ingredients to create extracts, and filters work best on raw liquid ingredients to create filtered items. Both typically result in items with a value of 30. The highest value items (60) are achieved by combining exactly TWO processed ingredients that share similar beneficial features, such as two 'filtered magical' liquids, two 'extracted mundane' liquids, or two 'extracted magical' liquids. Absolutely avoid combining more than two items, as this consistently results in 'overcomplicated' items with significantly reduced value. Also, avoid filtering items that have already been extracted or combined, as this leads to 'botched filtering' and reduced value. Do not use the vial on gas items.

Finally, combine one 'magical extracted liquid' with one 'mundane filtered liquid' (or vice versa) to achieve 100 points. Remember, only combine two items.
